lk.vivoxalabs.customstage

Class CustomStage

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.stage.Window
      • javafx.stage.Stage
        • lk.vivoxalabs.customstage.CustomStage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class CustomStage
extends javafx.stage.Stage
    A fully user customizable JavaFX Stage All of the customizing methods and methods which changing the appearance of the scene executed on FX-threads so user does not have to call these methods inside a Platform.runlater
    Version:
    1.1.1
    Author:
    oshan

      • dynamicDrawerEvent

        public void dynamicDrawerEvent(NavigationType type)
        This method shall be called if a dynamic navigationPane is in use. Will call either drawer.open() or drawer.hide() method depending on the drawer's current showing state.

        It is recommended to use this event especially if you're using NavigationType.TOP navigation, inorder to avoid the navigationPane from overlapping the title-bar on its drawer.hider() call.

        Parameters:
        type - the navigationPane which the event should be triggered for
